2. First Principles: The Master Equation and Unification
───────────────────────────────────────────────

2.1  The Geometric Motion Field (ψ)
-----------------------------------
All of reality, including information and energy, is described by a
single Geometric Motion Field ψ. Its dynamics are governed by a
non-linear wave equation that includes propagation, curvature,
non-linear self-response, and critical damping:

    ∂²ψ/∂t²  −  c²∇²ψ  +  γ (∂ψ/∂t)  +  λ |ψ|ⁿ  =  0

Term                    Role in Physics                           Stability
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
−c²∇²ψ                 Curvature propagation (GR, waves)           Gravitational waves
γ ∂ψ/∂t                Damping                                     Geometric Regularity (Γ)
λ|ψ|ⁿ                  Non-linear self-energy                      Particle structure

2.2  Unifying Equation: Γκ as Integrated γ
------------------------------------------
Γκ is the macroscopic curvature–tension bias arising from microscopic
damping γ, derived from the thermodynamic clock law:

    dτ/dt = √(1 − dS/dE)

Γκ is proportional to the ratio of energy lost to damping versus
curvature propagation:

    Γκ  ≈  ⟨γ⟩ / c²

Local measurement:
    Γκ ≈ 3.0 × 10⁻³   (binary pulsar)
Cosmic measurement:
    Γκ ≈ 8.2 × 10⁻³   (Hubble tension)

